headline: Garmin (GRMN) Q3 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Cliff Pemble: Thank you, Teri, and good morning, everyone.  As announced earlier today, Garmin achieved another quarter of outstanding financial results reflecting the strength of our unique, highly diversified business model.  Consolidated revenue increased 12% to nearly $1.8 billion, which is a new third quarter record, and we experienced strong double-digit revenue growth in three of our business segments.

headline: Garmin lifts annual profit outlook; outdoor unit weakness weighs on shares
summary: GPS device maker Garmin on Wednesday raised its adjusted profit forecast for the year, but reported a rise in operating expenses and decline in quarterly revenue from its outdoor and auto units. Shares of the company fell 10% in premarket trading following the results. Garmin, which offers GPS devices and technology used for fitness tracking, sports, aviation and marine sector, expects to benefit from the upgrades on its existing devices and new offerings launched during the reported quarter.

headline: Garmin: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: SCHAFFHAUSEN, Switzerland (AP) — Garmin Ltd. (GRMN) on Wednesday reported third-quarter profit of $401.6 million. The Schaffhausen, Switzerland-based company said it had profit of $2.08 per share. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring gains, came to $1.99 per share.
